<define-tag description>integer overflow</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>It was discovered that an integer overflow in the BGP dissector of tcpdump,
a powerful tool for network monitoring and data acquisition, may lead to
the execution of arbitrary code.</p>

<p>For the oldstable distribution (sarge) this problem has been fixed in
version 3.8.3-5sarge3.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (etch) this problem has been fixed in
version 3.9.5-2etch1.</p>

<p>For the unstable distribution (sid) this problem has been fixed in
version 3.9.5-3.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your tcpdump package.</p>
</define-tag>

